We also applied biaxial strains to see the effects on the structural and electronic properties of the vdW heterostructure (Table 3
                     ). The heterostructure became a metal for the tensile strain of 1%. Fig. 6
                      shows the layer-projected band structure for compressive strains up to −6%, indicating the shift of the CBM level to a point between K and Γ high-symmetry points. Besides, for compressive strains of 5.5% and −6%, the Sb monolayer mainly contributes to the VBM level of the heterostructure.
